Reuben Rapose 10:28 AM

Hey, addressing the points mentioned in the PDF below :


1. I understand the concern. The first image, (mobile screen) is an issue that happens only if when you size down on chrome from larger screen to a smaller screen because the states are being set for larger screen which are not being removed when you size down. This is a non-issue for any real world user. Please note that you need to reload the tab if you size down from a larger screen to a smaller one during testing.


For now, I'm preventing the desktop pop-up states from being set which means the pop-up will not be open on page load unless you click on one of the tabs, BUT this would make it easier for testing purposes as you wouldn't have to close the pop-up on desktop every time before sizing down to a smaller screen.


I'm attaching this video that demonstrates the degree of responsiveness I was able to achieve with the design you provided -> https://www.loom.com/share/dba43fd9c3fd482ba116d70ebe2ee9e7?sid=cc13d28c-a9fb-4fca-b780-e1b9d9650d64


Additionally, the figma design is not designed for screen sizes having width less than 1920. The ideal design size for web is around 1080 x 2400 which incorporates most browsers and screen sizes/ratios. I've tried my best to avoid collisions and size things appropriately on smaller screens. Eg. Since there was no space for the NFT avatar to remain in the center of a smaller screen, moving it to the side seemed like the only viable option at the time. I've also hid the Name of the NFT as seen in the video attached as I'm not sure where to put it on smaller screens so it would look appropriate... please advise.


2. Ah I think I missed this detail, I'll get that added.

Reuben Rapose 10:43 AM
